<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="416" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,907,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">
<bibRefCitation author="Luederwaldt, H." box="[199,427,943,967]" journalOrPublisher="Revista do Museu Paulista" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" pagination="207 - 216" part="20" refId="ref7939" refString="Luederwaldt, H. (1936) Notas complementares &quot; As especies Brasileiras do genero Pinotus &quot;. Revista do Museu Paulista, 20, 207 - 216." title="Notas complementares &quot; As especies Brasileiras do genero Pinotus" type="journal article" year="1936">Luederwaldt (1936)</bibRefCitation>
created the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Arrow" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[581,740,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis box="[581,601,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[621,740,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">calcaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group to accommodate 
<taxonomicName authority="(Arrow)" authorityName="Arrow" baseAuthorityName="Arrow" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1126,1392,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis box="[1126,1284,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. calcaratus</emphasis>
(Arrow)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Luederwaldt)" authorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexdentatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. sexdentatus</emphasis>
(Luederwaldt)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Luederwaldt)" authorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[512,876,980,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplicicornis">
<emphasis box="[512,705,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. simplicicornis</emphasis>
(Luederwaldt)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Vulcano, M. A. &amp; Pereira, F. S. &amp; Martinez, A." box="[887,1127,980,1004]" journalOrPublisher="Studia Entomologica" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" pagination="515 - 530" part="19" refId="ref8469" refString="Vulcano, M. A., Pereira, F. S. &amp; Martinez, A. (1976) Notas sobre Scarabaeoidea Americana (Col. Lamellicornia). Studia Entomologica, 19, 515 - 530." title="Notas sobre Scarabaeoidea Americana (Col. Lamellicornia)" type="journal article" year="1976">
Vulcano 
<emphasis box="[988,1038,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">et al</emphasis>
. (1976)
</bibRefCitation>
transfered 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Arrow" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1253,1406,980,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis box="[1253,1406,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. calcaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lucas" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[196,317,1016,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buqueti">
<emphasis box="[196,216,1017,1040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[233,317,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">buqueti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (then in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" box="[754,897,1016,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,897,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">Dichotomius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). With the transfer of the nominate species to another species group, the two remaining species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[754,924,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexdentatus">
<emphasis box="[754,924,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. sexdentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[991,1189,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplicicornis">
<emphasis box="[991,1189,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. simplicicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be placed in different species groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,907,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">
After examining the 
<typeStatus box="[442,540,1124,1148]" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">holotype</typeStatus>
(MZSP), we place 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[773,942,1124,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexdentatus">
<emphasis box="[773,942,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. sexdentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1029,1180,1124,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinicollis">
<emphasis box="[1029,1049,1125,1148]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1067,1180,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">crinicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group for the following reasons: it has a tooth on clypeal genal junction (
<figureCitation box="[850,921,1159,1183]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,209,1379]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[167,1403,195,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dichotomius eucranioides (A) black arrow indicating crenulated clypeal margin; D. sexdentatus (B) black arrow indicating tooth or protuberance on clypeogenal junction (this is also seen on D. eucranioides); D. nisus (C) black arrow indicating the asymmetry of the parameres; D. crinicollis (D) black arrows indicating pilosity on the hypomeron; D. superbus (E) white arrow indicating gibbosities on the pronotum; D. schiffleri (D. sericeus species group) (F) white arrow indicating a fovea on the posterior angle of the pronotum; D. speciosus (G) black arrows indicating cephalic transversal carina; D. agenor (H) black arrow indicating male cephalic carina; D. glaucus (D. carbornarius species group) (I) elytra microsculpture." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224053/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
B) and its hypomeron bears dense, long and curved, red pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[396,467,1196,1220]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,209,1379]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[167,1403,195,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dichotomius eucranioides (A) black arrow indicating crenulated clypeal margin; D. sexdentatus (B) black arrow indicating tooth or protuberance on clypeogenal junction (this is also seen on D. eucranioides); D. nisus (C) black arrow indicating the asymmetry of the parameres; D. crinicollis (D) black arrows indicating pilosity on the hypomeron; D. superbus (E) white arrow indicating gibbosities on the pronotum; D. schiffleri (D. sericeus species group) (F) white arrow indicating a fovea on the posterior angle of the pronotum; D. speciosus (G) black arrows indicating cephalic transversal carina; D. agenor (H) black arrow indicating male cephalic carina; D. glaucus (D. carbornarius species group) (I) elytra microsculpture." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224053/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D). After examining the 
<typeStatus box="[760,858,1196,1220]" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[904,1101,1196,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplicicornis">
<emphasis box="[904,1101,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. simplicicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(located in the NHML) and scrutinizing the original description, we place this species in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Harold" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[898,1014,1233,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agenor">
<emphasis box="[898,918,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[935,1014,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">agenor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group based on the cephalic horn in males constituting a transverse carina with a strong central tooth and two lateral teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1279,1268,1292]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,209,1379]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[167,1403,195,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dichotomius eucranioides (A) black arrow indicating crenulated clypeal margin; D. sexdentatus (B) black arrow indicating tooth or protuberance on clypeogenal junction (this is also seen on D. eucranioides); D. nisus (C) black arrow indicating the asymmetry of the parameres; D. crinicollis (D) black arrows indicating pilosity on the hypomeron; D. superbus (E) white arrow indicating gibbosities on the pronotum; D. schiffleri (D. sericeus species group) (F) white arrow indicating a fovea on the posterior angle of the pronotum; D. speciosus (G) black arrows indicating cephalic transversal carina; D. agenor (H) black arrow indicating male cephalic carina; D. glaucus (D. carbornarius species group) (I) elytra microsculpture." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224053/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
H), which is a shared characteristic with other species in this species group.
</paragraph>
